      • pollInterruptibly

        protected E pollInterruptibly()
                       throws InterruptedException
        Description copied from class: AbstractLockFreeBlockingQueue
        Removes the first element in the queue, allowing interruption. Since most lock-free queues won't have blocking operations during Queue.poll() (and thus not be interruptible), this method typically need not be overridden. But if any operations are interruptible, this method should be implemented to propagate that interruption, whereas the Queue.poll() method (due to its signature) must suppress it.
        Overrides:
        pollInterruptibly in class AbstractLockFreeBlockingQueue<E>
        Returns:
        the item removed from the queue or null if the queue is empty
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if the operation was interrupted
